<TITLE> Couple arrested for possession of heroin </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Bogra, May 10 (bdnews24.com)--The Bogra narcotics control department arrested a couple for possession of 150gms of heroin on Monday. The arrestees are Rahima Begum, daughter of Abul Kashem of Chaksutrapur area, and her husband Bishu, son of Abbas of Munsefpur village under Ashekpur union. Abdul Majid, the inspector of narcotics control, said that acting on secret information they had arrested the heroin smugglers from the house of one Harunur Rahman at Malatipur Pashchimpara area of Bogra town at around 11am. He claimed that Rahima was a heroin 'wholesaler'. The retailers used to buy heroin from her and sell them in different areas of the town. The alleged heroin smuggler Rahima said that she used to stay in a rented house at Malatinagar. Putu popularly known as a wholesale dealer of heroin, son of Majibar of Chaksutrapur, used to keep heroin with her and paid her Tk 1000 per week. Rahima's husband Bishu said that he was a transport worker. He knew nothing about his wife's involvement in narcotics smuggling. bd
